This paper deals with causality in databases, which is a topic closely related to database management systems and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses consistency-based diagnosis, database repairs, and view-update problems, which are all topics within the realm of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases). However, the paper also discusses abductive diagnosis, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses logical reasoning and consistency, which are topics within cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses software engineering and programming languages, which are topics within cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity), respectively.
